[![Photo by Richard Daniels, used with
permission](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2016/09/P1010725-Edit-800x534.jpg)](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2016/09/P1010725-Edit.jpg)

攝影：理查‧丹尼爾斯（Richard Daniels）。經授權使用。

_原文刊登於2016年9月12日。_

[理查‧丹尼爾斯](https://www.instagram.com/richard.james.daniels/)（Richard
Daniels）很想了解菲律賓籃球的普及程度，所以他從2011年開始了「[攝籃](http://www.richardjamesdaniels.com/basketball)」計畫，拍攝菲律賓鄉下地區籃球框的照片。

籃球是菲律賓最受歡迎的運動。儘管該國缺少運動設施，菲律賓人利用了巧妙的方法，在各種奇怪的地方設置籃框，像是在廢棄的土地上和街上。

當丹尼爾斯被問及是什麼激勵他投入「攝籃」這個紀錄計畫時，他告訴全球之聲，他對菲律賓籃球的普及度感到好奇，特別是在鄉下地方：

> As an Englishman and a football (soccer) fan I was always slightly confused
> as to why basketball was so popular here as opposed to football, which is
> massive throughout the rest of the world. My photo essay started off as a
> way to find out more about Filipino’s love of basketball through literally
> shooting hoops. I was also more interested in the aesthetic and the culture
> behind the grassroots courts and hoops of the poorer villages rather than
> the generic gymnasium courts in the more suburban areas.

>
> 身為英國人和足球迷，我總是有點困惑，為什麼籃球在這裡如此受歡迎，畢竟在全球其他地方較為主流的是足球。我的圖片故事透過真的「攝籃」來了解菲律賓人對籃球的熱愛。而且，相較於市郊的運動場館，我對平凡的球場、較貧困村莊的籃框背後的美感和文化比較有興趣。

[![Photo by Richard Daniels, used with
permission](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2016/09/P1050946-800x534.jpg)](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2016/09/P1050946.jpg)

攝影：理查‧丹尼爾斯（Richard Daniels）。經授權使用。

丹尼爾斯表示，他很驚訝地看到鄉下社區幾乎每個人都在打籃球：

> I hope that anyone who sees my project will be able to understand just how
> passionate the country is about basketball and how deeply entrenched the
> sport is in the local culture. I've seen a lot of hoops over the course of
> the project but it still amazes me to see these makeshift courts everywhere
> and anywhere and people of all ages playing – sometimes in only flip flops.

>
> 我希望看到這個計畫的人，都能了解這個國家對籃球的熱愛，以及這項運動在當地文化中的根深蒂固。在計畫過程中，我見過了很多籃框，但我依然很驚訝，到處都是臨時搭建的球場，各年齡層的人都在打籃球，有時候還只穿著夾腳拖鞋打球。

丹尼爾斯最喜歡的一張照片是當農夫們在整理種植土地時拍攝的：

> My favorite image is the basketball court that resembles something out of
> the Mad Max Movies. The structure looks like it’s made from bones! Also when
> I took the shot the fields were on fire as the farmers where clearing the
> land. I think it's called slash and burn farming. That was a pretty epic
> shot.

>
> 我最喜歡的照片是有一個籃球場很像電影《瘋狂麥斯》的場景，它的結構看起來像用骨頭做成的。而且，當我在拍照時，因為農夫利用一種叫做「刀耕火種」的技術在整理田地，球場正在起火。那真是一個壯麗的鏡頭。

[![Photo by Richard Daniels, used with
permission](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2016/09/P1110246-800x534.jpg)](https://globalvoices.org/wp-
content/uploads/2016/09/P1110246.jpg)

攝影：理查‧丹尼爾斯（Richard Daniels）。經授權使用。

丹尼爾斯希望在菲律賓其他地區找到更多有趣的籃框照片。同時，以下是一些丹尼爾斯拍下的照片，這些照片反映了菲律賓人渴望打籃球的堅韌和創造力。

